full_text: @llmunro I think of grief as luggage. At first, a huge steamer trunk that traps you underneath & you can‚Äôt move at all. It gets smaller & easier. It gets wheels, but the crappy  kind, and you just get frustrated. It never goes away entirely, but it gets easier (like a backpack). ‚ù§Ô∏è
